        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "The methods, insert, update, and delete in Zend_Db_Adapter_Abstract do not quote table or\ncolumn identifiers or support Zend_Db_Expr as values.\n\nThis makes the usefulness of these methods limited to very simple cases only,\nand potentially unsafe if the user assumes they work in a similar manner to methods of Zend_Db_Select.\n\nI propose that the table name and columns are quoted using quoteIdentifier(), and allow\nvalues supplied to insert()\/update() to be Zend_Db_Expr.\n\nI've already implemented this and can commit if there are no objections.\n"
        },
